    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nIf a writable file is in a non-writable directory, overwriting it yields E506, and force-overwriting it yields E207\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```\r\nsudo mkdir /weird-dir\r\nsudo touch /weird-dir/file\r\nsudo chmod 777 /weird-dir/file\r\nnvim --clean /weird-dir/file\r\n```\r\n\r\nVerify default:\r\n```\r\nset backupdir? backup? writebackup?\r\n  backupdir=.,~/.local/share/nvim/backup//\r\nnobackup\r\n  writebackup\r\n```\r\n\r\nMake changes, hit `:w`. That emits `E506: Can't write to backup file (add ! to override)`.\r\n\r\nTry `:w`. That emits `E207: Can't delete backup file`.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe first entry in backupdir is `.`, and that should fail. However, the second entry is `~/.local/share/nvim/backup//`, which (as per `:help backupdir`) should be attempted next, and does work. Indeed, setting backupdir to just `~/.local/share/nvim/backup//` (without `.,`) works around the issue.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.7.2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim 8.2.2434\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nUbuntu 23.11\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.35.0\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nUbuntu package manager",
